cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with deep domain adaptation, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of adversarial learning and deep networks suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with image datasets, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of multiple domain discriminators suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper deals with multimode structures, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
